HEADWORD: Ditheism
<hw>Di"the*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>theism</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>dith⟦eacute⟧isme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The doctrine of those who
maintain the existence of two gods or of two original principles (as in
Manicheism), one good and one evil; dualism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

